'''Gervonta Bryant Davis'''<ref>{{Cite web |last=Benson |first=Michael |date=2020-02-05 |title=Gervonta Davis arrested and charged after altercation with mother of his child |url=https://talksport.com/sport/665344/boxing-news-gervonta-davis-arrested-charged-video/ |access-date=2024-06-16 |website=talkSPORT}}</ref> ({{IPAc-en|dʒ|ər|ˈ|v|ɒ|n|t|eɪ}} {{respell|jər|VON|tay}}; born November 7, 1994), also known by his nickname "'''Tank'''", is an American [[professional boxer]]. He has held the [[World Boxing Association]] (WBA) [[lightweight]] title since 2023, having previously held the [[WBA (Regular)|Regular version]] from 2019 to 2023. He also held the [[International Boxing Federation]] (IBF) [[super featherweight]] title in 2017, the WBA super featherweight title ([[WBA (Super)|Super version]]) twice between 2018 and 2020, and the WBA [[super lightweight]] title (Regular version) in 2021.

As of May 2024, Davis is ranked as the world's second best active lightweight by [[ESPN]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Divisional rankings – The best top 10 fighters per division |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/21675272/divisional-rankings-best-top-10-fighters-per-division |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210424053730/https://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/21675272/divisional-rankings-best-top-10-fighters-per-division |archive-date=April 24, 2021 |access-date=May 24, 2021 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> first by the [[Transnational Boxing Rankings Board]],<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=TBRB rankings |url=https://tbrb.org/rankings |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20141206020332/http://www.tbrb.org/all-rankings/ |archive-date=December 6, 2014 |access-date=June 3, 2021 |website=Transnational Boxing Rankings Board}}</ref> and second by ''[[The Ring (magazine)|The Ring]]'' magazine.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ratings |url=https://www.ringtv.com/ratings/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090203095902/http://www.ringtv.com/ratings/ |archive-date=February 3, 2009 |access-date=October 29, 2021 |website=The Ring}}</ref>

==Early life==
Davis was raised in the [[Sandtown-Winchester, Baltimore|Sandtown-Winchester]] community in West Baltimore, one of the most crime-ridden areas of the city.<ref name=17Facts/> He attended [[Digital Harbor High School]], a local [[magnet school]], but dropped out to focus on his career. He later earned his secondary degree through a [[General Educational Development|GED]] program.<ref name=17Facts/>

==Amateur career==
Davis has been training at Upton Boxing Center since he was five years old.<ref name="17Facts">{{cite news|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/bal-17-facts-about-baltimore-boxing-champion-gervonta-davis-20170115-story.html|title=17 facts about Baltimore boxing champion Gervonta Davis|first=Mark|last=Selig|work=The Baltimore Sun|date=January 15, 2017|access-date=April 7, 2017|archive-date=May 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170507115326/http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/bal-17-facts-about-baltimore-boxing-champion-gervonta-davis-20170115-story.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=November 4, 2017|title=About – Gervonta Davis|url=http://gervontadavis.com/about|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171104171627/http://gervontadavis.com/about|archive-date=November 4, 2017|access-date=August 13, 2021}}</ref> Davis is trained by Calvin Ford who was the inspiration for the character [[Dennis "Cutty" Wise]] on the hit [[HBO]] television series, ''[[The Wire]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2015/04/a-boxing-school-in-baltimore-is-fighting-for-the-citys-soul|title=A boxing school in Baltimore is fighting for the city's soul|author=Chris Korman|date=April 29, 2015|work=USA Today|access-date=April 23, 2023|archive-date=February 5, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205142415/https://ftw.usatoday.com/2015/04/a-boxing-

